description:
NRCellCU: Table containing configuration parameters for 5G New Radio (NR) Cell CU (Control Unit) within a specific area.

- dateTime: Timestamp indicating when the data was recorded.
- Area_Name: Name of the geographical area where the cell is located.
- CellId: Unique identifier for the cell site.
- Id2: Redundant identifier, possibly a secondary key or alias for CellId.
- Id3: Another identifier, potentially referencing a related entity or function.
- vsDataType: Data type identifier, specifying the data as NRCellCU information.
- vsDataFormatVersion: Version of the data format used.
- NRCellCU.transmitSib2: Boolean indicating whether SIB2 (System Information Block 2) transmission is enabled.
- NRCellCU.userLabel: User-defined label for the cell.
- NRCellCU.threshServingLowP: Threshold for low power serving.
- NRCellCU.threshServingLowQ: Threshold for low quality serving.
- NRCellCU.sNonIntraSearchP: Parameter related to non-intra-frequency search (power).
- NRCellCU.sNonIntraSearchQ: Parameter related to non-intra-frequency search (quality).
- NRCellCU.primaryPLMNId: Primary Public Land Mobile Network (PLMN) identifier.
- NRCellCU.pmUeIntraFreqEnabled: Boolean indicating whether PMU (Power Management Unit) intra-frequency is enabled.
- NRCellCU.cellLocalId: Local identifier for the cell within the site.
- NRCellCU.nRCellCUId: Unique identifier for the NR Cell CU.
- NRCellCU.tHystNormal: Hysteresis threshold parameter.
- NRCellCU.transmitSib5: Boolean indicating whether SIB5 transmission is enabled.
- NRCellCU.qHystSfMedium: Quality hysteresis for medium conditions.
- NRCellCU.cellState: Current operational state of the cell (e.g., ACTIVE, INACTIVE).
- NRCellCU.tEvaluation: Parameter related to cell evaluation.
- NRCellCU.transmitSib4: Boolean indicating whether SIB4 transmission is enabled.
- NRCellCU.serviceState: Service state of the cell (e.g., IN_SERVICE, OUT_OF_SERVICE).
- NRCellCU.nrdcMnCellProfileRef: Reference to the NR DC (Distributed Coordination) MN (Management Node) cell profile.
- NRCellCU.nCellChangeMedium: Cell change parameter for medium conditions.
- NRCellCU.trStSaCellProfileRef: Reference to the TR ST SA (Transmission and Reception System State) cell profile.
- NRCellCU.mcpcPSCellProfileRef: Reference to the MCPC (Multi-Carrier Power Control) PS (Physical Signal) cell profile.
- NRCellCU.sNSSAIList: List of S-NSSAI (Slice-Specific Network Slice Selection Assistance Information) identifiers.
- NRCellCU.mdtEnabled: Boolean indicating whether MDT (Mobility Data Transfer) is enabled.
- NRCellCU.nCI: Network Cell Identity (NCI).
- NRCellCU.hiPrioDetEnabled: Boolean indicating whether high priority detection is enabled.
- NRCellCU.pwsEmergencyAreaIdList: List of Public Warning System (PWS) emergency area identifiers.
- NRCellCU.mcpcPSCellEnabled: Boolean indicating whether MCPC PS cell is enabled.
- NRCellCU.qHyst: Quality hysteresis parameter.
- NRCellCU.nRTAC: NR Tracking Area Code (TAC).
- NRCellCU.nRFrequencyRef: Reference to the NR frequency band configuration.
- NRCellCU.nCellChangeHigh: Cell change parameter for high conditions.
- NRCellCU.mcfbCellProfileRef: Reference to the MCFB (Multi-Cell Frequency Band) cell profile.
- NRCellCU.ueMCCellProfileRef: Reference to the UE (User Equipment) MC cell profile.
- NRCellCU.mdtCellProfileRef: Reference to the MDT cell profile.
- NRCellCU.pmUeIntraFreqCellProfileRef: Reference to the PMU intra-frequency cell profile.
- NRCellCU.mcpcPCellProfileRef: Reference to the MCPC PC (Physical Channel) cell profile.
- NRCellCU.intraFreqMCCellProfileRef: Reference to the intra-frequency MC cell profile.
- NRCellCU.qHystSfHigh: Quality hysteresis for high conditions.
- NRCellCU.reservedBy: Information on entity reserving this cell configuration.
- NRCellCU.pSCellCapable: Boolean indicating whether the cell is capable of PS cell operation.
- NRCellCU.trStPSCellProfileRef: Reference to the TR ST PS cell profile.
- NRCellCU.pLMNIdList: List of PLMN identifiers.
- NRCellCU.mcpcPCellEnabled: Boolean indicating whether MCPC PC cell is enabled.
